Ourouparia is a flowering plant in the family of Madders.  It is used as a natural source for dye.

In the plant kingdom, it is in the division of flowering plants ([[angiosperms]]), class [[Rosopsida]], subclass [[Lamiidae]], superorder Gentiananae, order Rubiales, suborder Rubiineae, family Rubiaceae ([[Madder]]), and genus Ourouparia. 	

Ourouparia is also the longest English word that uses the consonants P and R, and no other consonants.

